@ag3nt-z3 I just ran a test against the asset, and I am still able to gain Remote Code Execution over the server. In the screenshot you can see my payload requested the the asset to send a ping command to my server address again, and I received requests from █████████.

I've reported this issue to other bug bounty programs and there has been some stability issues with the Microsoft patch released. I was also made aware that Microsoft released two versions of the patch because the first release did not fix the issue. If the asset owner in deploying from a patch management system that uses a update repository, it could have the older version of the patch. I would have the asset owner confirm the patch is the newest version, or bypass the patch management system and download the patch directly from Microsoft.

Please let me know if I can help further.
